          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a manual for use by priests or householders performing different kinds of rites. The first is called Vaiśvadevavidhi and consists of offerings to various Hindu deities; the second is called Nityaśraddhavidhi and consists of offerings to one's ancestors. Text contains a collection of various mantras to various deities to be recited during the various rites. There is a diagram with 23 numbered mantras written in red ink (f. 3v).</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Vaiśvadaivikaśrāddhavidhi</title>
